 People look at the light decorations at VanDusen Botanical Garden in Vancouver, British Columbia, Canada, Nov. 26, 2021. The "Festival of Lights" returned Friday night after being postponed last year due to COVID-19 pandemic. Over a million lights are seen in the 15 acres of VanDusen Botanical Garden. (Photo by Liang Sen/Xinhua)  The light decorations are seen at VanDusen Botanical Garden in Vancouver, British Columbia, Canada, Nov. 26, 2021. The "Festival of Lights" returned Friday night after being postponed last year due to COVID-19 pandemic. Over a million lights are seen in the 15 acres of VanDusen Botanical Garden. (Photo by Liang Sen/Xinhua)  People walk past the light decorations at VanDusen Botanical Garden in Vancouver, British Columbia, Canada, Nov. 26, 2021. The "Festival of Lights" returned Friday night after being postponed last year due to COVID-19 pandemic. Over a million lights are seen in the 15 acres of VanDusen Botanical Garden. (Photo by Liang Sen/Xinhua)  People look at the light decorations at VanDusen Botanical Garden in Vancouver, British Columbia, Canada, Nov. 26, 2021. The "Festival of Lights" returned Friday night after being postponed last year due to COVID-19 pandemic. Over a million lights are seen in the 15 acres of VanDusen Botanical Garden. (Photo by Liang Sen/Xinhua)  People look at the light decorations at VanDusen Botanical Garden in Vancouver, British Columbia, Canada, Nov. 26, 2021. The "Festival of Lights" returned Friday night after being postponed last year due to COVID-19 pandemic. Over a million lights are seen in the 15 acres of VanDusen Botanical Garden. (Photo by Liang Sen/Xinhua)  A resident takes photos of the light decorations at VanDusen Botanical Garden in Vancouver, British Columbia, Canada, Nov. 26, 2021. The "Festival of Lights" returned Friday night after being postponed last year due to COVID-19 pandemic. Over a million lights are seen in the 15 acres of VanDusen Botanical Garden. (Photo by Liang Sen/Xinhua) 